Done. Here's what was implemented across 2 files:

**`app/auth.py`** — `require_api_key` now reads the `X-API-Key` header, validates it against `VALID_API_KEYS`, raises `HTTP 401` if missing or invalid, returns the username on success.

**`app/main.py`** — six changes:
- **`GET /tasks`** — added optional `status`, `priority`, `assigned_to` query params (all combinable, filters to exact matches) plus `page` (default 1) and `page_size` (default 20) for pagination
- **`POST /tasks`** — requires auth via `Depends(require_api_key)`, validates `project_id` exists (404 if not), auto-generates `id = max(...) + 1`, returns `201` with the created task
- **`PUT /tasks/{task_id}`** — requires auth, applies partial updates (only non-None fields), returns 404 if not found
- **`DELETE /tasks/{task_id}`** — requires auth, removes the task, returns `204`, returns 404 if not found
